\begin_layout Standard
However, the notion of status most commonly used in literature - where it
 is seen merely as a long-term characteristics of the consumer - is hardly
 one that can relate social identity with consumption.
 The view of status as a static characteristic - which allows the studies
 in sociology and health sciences to use status as simply a vector education
