 context of consumption.
 If status were only accumulated over a sufficiently long-term, how can
 there be any utility from status consumption? The paradox is trivially
 resolved if one considers that status is subject to change with consumption
 - just the way it is shaped by income or education.
 This dynamic view of status - provided by Coleman
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ColemanSocialTheory1990"
literal "true"

\end_inset

